        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="881" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d881">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.461/10–1746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-24T15:00:00-05:00">October 24, 1946—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>925. Dept of opinion (Urtel 1679, Oct 17, 11 a.m.) we should not delay further
                    reopening Harbin and it is hoped final arrangements will be made for Clubb
                    proceeed there in near future. Details flight should be communicated to Chou
                    En-lai sufficiently in advance to enable him (Sent Nanking, repeated Mukden for
                    Clubb) notify local authorities Harbin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
